The White House released a readout of President Obama's meeting with business leaders on July 31, 2009. The President invited Ivan Seidenberg, CEO of Verizon and Chairman of the Business Roundtable, Mike Duke, CEO of Wal-Mart, Dan DiMicco, CEO of Nucor, and Howard Schultz, CEO of Starbucks, to join him for lunch. The meeting lasted for 75 minutes and covered topics such as the state of the economy, health care reform, and energy. The President and his economic team expressed their intention to continue holding informal meetings with business leaders to gather their input.